'''Gregory Everett "Greg" Proops''' (born [[October 3]], [[1950s|1959]]), best known for his improvisational comedy on the first two incarnations of TV's ''Whose Line is it Anyway?'', was the voice of [[Fodesinbeed Annodue|Fode]] in [[Star Wars: Episode I The Phantom Menace|''Star Wars'': Episode I ''The Phantom Menace'']], the video game spin-offs [[Star Wars: Episode I Racer|''Star Wars'': Episode I ''Racer'']] and ''[[Kinect Star Wars]]'', and ''[[LEGO Star Wars: The Freemaker Adventures]]'' episode seven, "[[Race on Tatooine]]." He voiced another race announcer, [[Jak Sivrak]], in ''[[Star Wars Resistance]]''. Proops also voiced the character of [[Tal Merrik]] in [[Star Wars: The Clone Wars|''The Clone Wars'']] [[The Clone Wars: Season Two|Season Two]]. He currently works with Yahoo! News and hosts a podcast called ''The Smartest Man in the World''.

